The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNN) in vision, speech, and language processing, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on reducing energy consumption and increasing performance, which is related to the sub-category of energy-efficient computing (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of approximate memory, which can affect the reliability of the system, and thus falls under the sub-category of system reliability (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for retraining DNNs, which is related to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on different hardware architectures, which falls under the sub-category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
